Spectrum of cystic tumors of the pancreas. The pathologic and clinical classification, as well as the behavior, of cystic tumors of the pancreas has been the subject of controversy. We retrospectively reviewed 50 patients with a diagnosis of cystic tumor of the pancreas observed at The Johns Hopkins Hospital from 1984 to 1991. These tumors were classified into three broad groups: I, cystadenoma II, cystadenocarcinoma